From: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
Date: Thu, 1 Dec 2011 23:49:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mm: migration: clean up unmap_and_move()
References: Reduce major stalls due to THP and compaction
Patch-mainline: yes
Git-commit: 0dabec93de633a87adfbbe1d800a4c56cd19d73b

unmap_and_move() is one a big messy function.  Clean it up.

Signed-off-by: Minchan Kim <minchan.kim@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: KOSAKI Motohiro <kosaki.motohiro@jp.fujitsu.com>
Cc: Johannes Weiner <hannes@cmpxchg.org>
Cc: KAMEZAWA Hiroyuki <kamezawa.hiroyu@jp.fujitsu.com>
Cc: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
Cc: Rik van Riel <riel@redhat.com>
Cc: Michal Hocko <mhocko@suse.cz>
Cc: Andrea Arcangeli <aarcange@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Andrew Morton <akpm@linux-foundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Linus Torvalds <torvalds@linux-foundation.org>
---
 mm/migrate.c |   68 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------------------
 1 files changed, 40 insertions(+), 28 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/migrate.c b/mm/migrate.c
index c9a54a9..6c82460 100644
--- a/mm/migrate.c
+++ b/mm/migrate.c
